Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer for sale via Public Auction Shop 1 and Shop 2, 356 George Street, Waterloo. These two shops are within the newly completed George and Allen development. The two shops are to be offered separately and both benefit from the corner position on George and Allen Streets.

The details of each opportunity is listed below:


Shop 1

- Tenant - Pizza Deli
- Size 139sqm*
- Lease term 5 + 5 + 5
- Net Annual Rent - $62,500pa ex GST*
- Tenant responsible for 100% of all outgoings
- 1 car space
- Brand new contemporary Italian restaurant fitout

Shop 2

- Tenant - Happy Wheels
- Size 190sqm*
- Lease term 5 + 3 + 3
- Net Annual Rent - $78,679pa ex GST*
- Tenant responsible for 100% of all outgoings
- 1 car space
- Brand new contemporary Bike shop and repair fitout

The suites are located on the corner of Allen and George Street, in the thriving and gentrifying Waterloo area. The suites are in close proximity to the new Green Square Town Centre and Train Station. Extensive tenant fitout within both tenancies.

*Approx

* Unique opportunity: 4 storey mixed use building
* 3 storeys of commercial office space. NLA 1,656sqm (approx) (typical floor plate 552sqm approx)
* 267sqm (approx) top floor luxury 4 bedroom penthouse
* 56sqm (approx) of NLA for retail
* 25 car parking spaces
* Offered with vacant possession
* Ability to lease and hold, or subdivide and sell down S.T.C.A.
* Excellent opportunity for owner occupiers or investors
* Close to complete with scope to add 'personal touch'

For Sale by Tender Closing 13th October 2011

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Attention: Owner Occupiers or Investors - Almost Complete City Fringe Freehold

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Two retail shops + a 3 bedroom apartment

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agents are pleased to present to you, 39-41 Botany Road, a two-storey mixed use investment comprising two ground floor retail shops and a three-bedroom shop top apartment. One retail shop is currently vacant and the other occupied by a Vietnamese bakery, the apartment is leased by residential tenants.

The investment capitalises on its positioning amongst the wealth of amenity afforded by its proximity to Redfern Train Station. The property has a large 12m* street frontage along Botany Road with exposure to high pedestrian and vehicular traffic and benefits from the following key attributes. 

- Two ground floor retail shops plus a three-bedroom apartment
- Net lettable area of 290sqm*
- Mixed use investment ideal for owner occupiers or investors
- 650m* from Redfern Train Station 
- Within 450m* of the Australian Technology Park and only 150m* to the future Waterloo Metro Station 
- Within a high traffic commercial precinct well positioned for growth


For any further information on the property please contact the exclusive agents.

TENANTED BY THE WORLD'S FASTEST GROWING GYM FRANCHISE

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present Lot 2, 17-19 Danks Street, Waterloo. This property is currently tenanted by one of the world’s largest gym franchises, Orangetheory Fitness, on a long 10-year lease to 2027. Situated in the burgeoning suburb of Waterloo, the property is a secure retail investment supported by an international tenant, all whilst being just a short distance from Sydney CBD.

Lot 2, 17-19 Danks Street, Waterloo benefits from the following key attributes: 

- Tenanted by Orangetheory Fitness, a global giant in the fitness industry with over 1,000 locations worldwide 
- Long term 10 year lease with options to 2037
- Secure retail investment with a net passing income of $114,735 per annum* 
- Total strata area: 397sqm*
- Set to benefit from the future Waterloo Metro Station 
- Rapidly growing suburb with a number of high density developments under construction or in planning 
- Surrounded by an abundance of shopping amenity 
- The future Green Square development in Zetland is expected to bring 61,000 new residents and 22,000 new workers to the area by 2030 
- Just 1.9km* to Sydney CBD 

Lot 2, 17-19 Danks Street, Waterloo will be offered for sale via public auction on Tuesday 30 October 2018 at 10.30am.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

*All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.
